I just came to know about **istringstream** function and its amazing for string iteration in C++. 

First step is to count differrence of dots(.) in both string. 
Now, if we have string with different number of dots, let us add zeros to the end of short list. Then replace all dots with space to make it compatible for our istringstream function.
Finally, we need to iterate over both string and simply compare every instance of both strings. 
**Note** that preceeding zeros are automatically handled. 
```
class Solution {
public:
    int compareVersion(string version1, string version2) {
        int dif=count(version1.begin(),version1.end(),'.')-count(version2.begin(),version2.end(),'.');
        while(dif>0){
            version2+=".0";
            dif--;
        }
        while(dif<0){
            version1+=".0";
            dif++;
        }
        replace(version1.begin(),version1.end(),'.',' ');
        replace(version2.begin(),version2.end(),'.',' ');
        istringstream s1(version1);
        istringstream s2(version2);
        for(int n1,n2 ; s1>>n1,s2>>n2 ;)
            if(n1>n2)
                return 1;
            else if(n1<n2)
                return -1; 
        return 0;
    }
};
```
Complexity: time complexity is O(n+m), where n and m are lengths of our strings, space complexity O(1) since we iterate over string.

